    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1923-09-18T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1923-09-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="124"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d124">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.348 Z 4/44</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in Great Britain</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wheeler</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="91" xml:id="d124fn91">The same instruction, <hi
                            rend="italic">mutatis mutandis</hi>, was sent to the diplomatic
                        representatives in Belgium, France, Portugal, Spain, Switzerland, and the
                        Netherlands.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1923-09-18">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 18, 1923</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The Department has been informed by the Secretary
                    of the Navy that the rigid airship <hi rend="italic">ZR–3</hi>, now building in
                    Friedrichshafen, Germany, for the Government of the United States, will fly to
                    Lake-hurst, New Jersey, sometime between the fifteenth of November and the first
                    of December, 1923. The probable route of the ship will be from Friedrichshafen
                    across France to the Bay of Biscay, thence across Cape Finisterre, the Azores
                    and possibly the Bermuda Islands. It appears that the route cannot be absolutely
                    determined at this time, however, and it is possible that the airship may fly
                    over The Netherlands, Belgium, Switzerland, France, Spain, Portugal and Great
                    Britain before crossing the Atlantic Ocean.</p>
                <p>You are requested to advise the Government to which you are accredited of this
                    proposed flight with a view to securing its permission for the airship to pass
                    over its territory, and to report by cable.</p>
                <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                <closer>For the Secretary of State:<lb/>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Leland Harrison</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
